        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 24. Ronzotherium heissigi sp. nov. from Vendèze (late early Oligocene, France). A–D. Mandible MNHN.F.LIM181. A. Occlusal view. B. Lateral view. C. With left p2–p4 and m2–3 in labial view. View. D. Right p2–m3 in lingual view. – E. Skull MNHN.F.LIM181, belonging to the same individual as the mandible, close-up view of P2–M3 in occlusal view. Scale bars: 2 cm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4945928/files/figure.png" .

